AWS EC2 Instance Setup with Apache Web Server
Practical Steps
1. Sign in to AWS Console
Open AWS Management Console.
Login with your AWS account.
2. Open EC2 Service
Search for EC2 in the AWS search bar.
Click on EC2 Dashboard.
3. Launch a New Instance
Click Launch Instance.
Fill the following details:
Name: myEC2server
AMI (Operating System): Ubuntu Server 24.04
Instance Type: t3.micro
4. Create Key Pair
Click Create new key pair.
Enter:
Key Pair Name: mykey
Key Pair Type: RSA
Private Key Format: .pem
Download and save the .pem file safely.
5. Configure Security Group
Allow these rules:
Type
Port
Source
SSH
22
Anywhere
HTTP
80
Anywhere
Then click:
Launch Instance
Connect to EC2 Instance
6. Open Instance
Go to Instances
Select your instance
Click Connect
Choose EC2 Instance Connect
Click Connect
Commands to Run in Terminal
7. Update Packages
Bash
sudo apt update
8. Install Apache Web Server
Bash
sudo apt install apache2 -y
9. Start Apache Service
Bash
sudo systemctl start apache2
10. Enable Apache Service
Bash
sudo systemctl enable apache2
11. Go to Web Directory
Bash
cd /var/www/html
12. Create/Edit HTML File
Bash
sudo nano index.html
13. Write HTML Code
Example:
HTML
<html>
<head>
<title>My AWS Server</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Welcome to My EC2 Server</h1>
</body>
</html>
Save the file:
Press CTRL + O
Press Enter
Press CTRL + X
View Website
14. Copy Public IPv4 Address
Go back to EC2 Instances
Copy Public IPv4 Address
Example:
Plain text
http://your-public-ip
Paste it into browser.
